Overview Notes: Monitor BP levels and if persistently high then book an appointment with GP. Supplement with magnesium and omega 3's and manage stress levels
Comment Key: ChronicMedicationList
Comment Value: antihypertensive
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Age 58
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Monitor BP levels and if persistently high then book an appointment with GP. Supplement with magnesium and omega 3's and manage stress levels
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level - supplement with D3 5000iu daily and recheck level in 3 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/dl
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Monitor BP levels and if persistently high then book an appointment with GP. Supplement with magnesium and omega 3's and manage stress levels
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: None
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Highly motivated individual with a proactive stance towards life
Excellent blood results

Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level - supplement with D3 5000iu daily and recheck level in 3 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/dl
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Fair skin, some sun damage but sees dermatologist regularly
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Age 58
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.

Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Highly motivated individual with a proactive stance towards life
Excellent blood results
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: All normal, suboptimal vitamin D but within normal
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Overview Notes: Monitor for any urinary symptoms. Drink a lot of water to flush the kidneys and continue with over the counter treatment that you started yesterday. Repeat dipstix in a few days.
Comment Key: LabTestRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Your cholesterol is very well controlled. Consider weaning zuvamor.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: -Continue managing & monitoring the chronic conditions as you have been. 
-Continue screening for cancer as advised.

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level - supplement with D3 5000iu daily and recheck level in 3 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/dl

Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Monitor for any urinary symptoms. Drink a lot of water to flush the kidneys and continue with over the counter treatment that you started yesterday. Repeat dipstix in a few days.

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Taking zuvamor for cholesterol management
Possible low grade urinary tract infection
BP marginally raised
Due for a PAP smear and mammogram

-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Suboptimal vitamin D level - supplement with D3 5000iu daily and recheck level in 3 months aiming for a level of 50 to 80ng/dl
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: None
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Taking zuvamor for cholesterol management
Possible low grade urinary tract infection
BP marginally raised
Due for a PAP smear and mammogram
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Comment Key: VitalsNote
Comment Value: Marginally raised BP, good body composition
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Keep up to date with cancer screening.
-Evening Primrose oil may help ease some of the menopausal symptoms you occasionally experience.
Overview Notes: Monitor BP levels and if persistently high then book an appointment with GP. Supplement with magnesium and omega 3's and manage stress levels
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements

Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)

Clinical Recommendations: -The right ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz. The left ear has mild hearing loss at 500Hz & 4kHz. A full audiogram is recommended to establish the cause of the hearing loss & how to manage it. Please see an audiologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: -Cancer screening is important as you grow older. Prioritise these screenings & look out for any changes or abnormalities.
Overview Notes: Monitor BP levels and if persistently high then book an appointment with GP. Supplement with magnesium and omega 3's and manage stress levels
Comment Key: WomensHealthRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: +25 leu, trace nitrates in urine (asymptomatic)
